properties.areaDesc: Waters from San Mateo point to the Mexican Border Extending 30 to 60 nm out including San Clemente Island; Coastal Waters from San Mateo Point to the Mexican Border and out to 30 nm
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 1 at 11:30AM PST until February 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts to 40 kt and
combined seas of 12 to 20 ft.

* WHERE...Inner and outer coastal waters. Highest winds and seas
in the outer coastal waters.

* WHEN...From Sunday afternoon through noon Monday. Highest winds
and seas will occur Sunday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 2 PM SUNDAY TO NOON PST MONDAY
